<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1085,588,867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1851" box="[292,411,588,609]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[292,411,588,609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Blepharella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1863" box="[680,795,588,610]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Exoristinae">Exoristinae</taxonomicName>
and tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="(HERTING 1984)" baseAuthorityName="HERTING" baseAuthorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Goniini">
Goniini (
<bibRefCitation author="HERTING B" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 228" refId="ref1635" refString="HERTING B. (1984): Catalogue of Palaearctic Tachinidae (Diptera). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde Serie A 369: 1 - 228." type="journal article" year="1984">HERTING 1984</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The genus can be recognized by the keys given by 
<bibRefCitation author="MESNIL L" box="[813,964,617,638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="49 - 104" refId="ref1663" refString="MESNIL L. P. (1949): Larvaevorinae (Tachininae). - In: LINDNER E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaarktischen Region, Schweitzerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 49 - 104." type="book chapter" year="1949">MESNIL (1949</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="MESNIL L" box="[979,1031,617,639]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="105 - 160" refId="ref1705" refString="MESNIL L. P. (1950): Larvaevorinae (Tachininae). - In: LINDNER E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaarktischen Region, Schweitzerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 105 - 160." type="book chapter" year="1950">1950</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="CROSSKEY R" box="[178,366,646,668]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="189 - 337" refId="ref1323" refString="CROSSKEY R. W. (1984): Annotated keys to the genera of Tachinidae (Diptera) found in tropical and southern Africa. - Annals of the Natal Museum 26: 189 - 337." type="journal article" year="1984">CROSSKEY (1984)</bibRefCitation>
. The specimens collected also would run to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1851" box="[847,966,645,666]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[847,966,645,666]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Blepharella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the key provided by TSCHORSNIG &amp; RICHTER (1998), except for the fact that the scutellum is partly reddish. This is of course only relevant at specific level. In several species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1851" box="[178,297,731,752]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[178,297,731,752]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Blepharella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the prosternum is bare, in contrast to the original state of this feature in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1863" box="[286,405,759,781]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Exoristinae">Exoristinae</taxonomicName>
. This secondary loss of setulae on the prosternum is found in a few other genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1863" box="[346,461,788,810]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Exoristinae">Exoristinae</taxonomicName>
as well (for instance 
<emphasis box="[692,789,788,809]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Oswaldia</emphasis>
ROBINEAU- DESVOIDY 1863, 
<emphasis box="[178,240,816,837]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Hebia</emphasis>
ROBINEAU- DESVOIDY 1830 and 
<taxonomicName authority="MACQUART 1834" authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1834" box="[576,860,816,838]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Masicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,671,817,838]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Masicera</emphasis>
MACQUART 1834
</taxonomicName>
). The known hosts for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1851" box="[178,294,845,866]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[178,294,845,866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Blepharella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are caterpillars of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[477,599,845,867]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
, mostly 
<taxonomicName authority="(CROSSKEY 1984)" baseAuthorityName="CROSSKEY" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[681,968,845,867]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Noctuidae (
<bibRefCitation author="CROSSKEY R" box="[795,960,845,867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="189 - 337" refId="ref1323" refString="CROSSKEY R. W. (1984): Annotated keys to the genera of Tachinidae (Diptera) found in tropical and southern Africa. - Annals of the Natal Museum 26: 189 - 337." type="journal article" year="1984">CROSSKEY 1984</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1086,881,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1851" box="[303,422,881,902]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[303,422,881,902]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Blepharella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been revised on a worldwide scale by 
<bibRefCitation author="MESNIL L" box="[918,1082,881,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="209 - 256" refId="ref1747" refString="MESNIL L. P. (1952): Larvaevorinae (Tachininae). - In: LINDNER E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaarktischen Region, Schweitzerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 209 - 256." type="book chapter" year="1952">MESNIL (1952)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="CROSSKEY R" box="[178,365,910,932]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="822 - 882" refId="ref1271" refString="CROSSKEY R. W. (1980): Family Tachinidae. - In: CROSSKEY R. W. &amp; L. PAPP (eds), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 822 - 882." type="book chapter" year="1980">CROSSKEY (1980)</bibRefCitation>
transferred many species from related genera to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1851" box="[907,1026,910,931]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[907,1026,910,931]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Blepharella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The varieties of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Corti" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[307,421,939,960]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setigera">
<emphasis box="[307,421,939,960]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">B. setigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="MESNIL L" box="[586,743,938,960]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="209 - 256" refId="ref1747" refString="MESNIL L. P. (1952): Larvaevorinae (Tachininae). - In: LINDNER E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaarktischen Region, Schweitzerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 209 - 256." type="book chapter" year="1952">MESNIL (1952)</bibRefCitation>
were raised to species level by 
<bibRefCitation author="CROSSKEY R" box="[178,362,967,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="822 - 882" refId="ref1271" refString="CROSSKEY R. W. (1980): Family Tachinidae. - In: CROSSKEY R. W. &amp; L. PAPP (eds), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 822 - 882." type="book chapter" year="1980">CROSSKEY (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="MESNIL L" box="[371,522,967,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="37 - 57" refId="ref1789" refString="MESNIL L. P. (1967): Tachinaires palearctiques inedits (Diptera). - Mushi 41: 37 - 57." type="journal article" year="1967">MESNIL (1967)</bibRefCitation>
added 
<taxonomicName authority="MESNIL, 1967" authorityName="MESNIL" authorityYear="1967" box="[596,828,967,989]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[596,679,967,988]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">B. nigra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MESNIL L" box="[685,828,967,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="37 - 57" refId="ref1789" refString="MESNIL L. P. (1967): Tachinaires palearctiques inedits (Diptera). - Mushi 41: 37 - 57." type="journal article" year="1967">MESNIL, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[889,950,967,988]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[178,1085,1003,1139]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">
Adding all up, currently 43 species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MACQUART" authorityYear="1851" box="[580,699,1003,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[580,699,1003,1024]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">Blepharella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are considered valid. The vast majority of these, 41 species, occur in the Afrotropical region (
<bibRefCitation author="CROSSKEY R" box="[769,940,1032,1054]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="822 - 882" refId="ref1271" refString="CROSSKEY R. W. (1980): Family Tachinidae. - In: CROSSKEY R. W. &amp; L. PAPP (eds), Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region. British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 822 - 882." type="book chapter" year="1980">CROSSKEY 1980</bibRefCitation>
). One species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1851" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1851" box="[178,475,1060,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis box="[178,295,1060,1082]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">B. lateralis</emphasis>
Macquart, 1851
</taxonomicName>
, occurs in both the Oriental and the Australasian region (
<bibRefCitation author="CROSSKEY R" box="[185,357,1089,1110]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 221" refId="ref1178" refString="CROSSKEY R. W. (1973): A conspectus of the Tachinidae (Diptera) of Australia, including keys to the supraspecific taxa and taxonomic and host catalogues. - Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, Supplement 21: 1 - 221." type="journal article" year="1973">CROSSKEY 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="CROSSKEY R" box="[370,422,1089,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 357" refId="ref1229" refString="CROSSKEY R. W. (1976): A taxonomic conspectus of the Tachinidae (Diptera) of the Oriental region. - Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, Supplement 26: 1 - 357." type="journal article" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
) and one species, the above mentioned 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MESNIL" authorityYear="1967" box="[843,929,1089,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[843,929,1089,1110]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="540">B. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in the eastern Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation author="MESNIL L" box="[303,444,1117,1139]" pageId="1" pageNumber="540" pagination="37 - 57" refId="ref1789" refString="MESNIL L. P. (1967): Tachinaires palearctiques inedits (Diptera). - Mushi 41: 37 - 57." type="journal article" year="1967">MESNIL 1967</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
